🥳👏🤩🎆 Great news! Our vendors have asked that we extend the market into October! So we will now be there every Friday through October 30th! 🎃

Reading Athletic Boosters will be selling spirit wear!

Sase Bean - organic coffee and tea
Strong's Brick Oven Pizzeria- Italian bread and red sauce
Susan's Stitchery - masks, baby quilts and blankets, etc.

As a boosters organization, we wanted to say thank you to everyone for who came out and purchased spirit wear and supported the Reading Athletic Boosters. Also, thank you to everyone for wearing masks and practicing social distancing!

We will be having our next Spirit Wear Sale at the Reading Farmers Market this coming Friday (8/21/2020) starting at 3:30 pm. We will be accepting payments by cash, check, and Venmo. We look forward to seeing more of RBD Nation at the Reading Farmers Market.

As we move forward through these new times, any donations to Reading Athletic Boosters would be greatly appreciated. Donations can be made through Venmo.

Venmo Info: @RBD-AthleticBoosters

Again, a big thank you to our awesome community for supporting the Reading Athletic Boosters. As always, GO RBD!!!

Rhonda Nickol Joe Ellis

Reading Community City Schools
August 13 at 3:42 PM ·

At the Board work session held on August 5, VSWC architects presented two options for the athletic field at the Hilltop Elementary site.

VSWC architects have been working with the Board of Education’s building and grounds committee along with Reading High School baseball coach RJ Hayes and softball coach Amanda Shinkle on plans for the new fields.

The building and grounds committee has narrowed down the options for the athletic fields and the costs associated with completion. It is important to note that funding for this project is not through our general operating dollars but through funds that can only be used on improvements to the Hilltop property.

Of the two final options, the building…

Reading Athletic Boosters

Parents and Players,

On Monday, March 9th at 7:00pm any player or parent interested in playing football next year must attend the informational meeting for the upcoming season. Details will include schedule, high school and middle school training information, as well as introduction of staff and mission for the year. There will be a sign up for middle school and high school players during school leading up to the meeting on the 9th. I want to remind all players that if you are not currently playing a winter sport or trying out for a spring sport that they are expected to be in weights Monday to Thursday immediately after school until 4:30p.m. Looking forward to getting started and see everyone there.

Thank you,
Thank you,
Cody Reardon

shared_text:
Reading Blue Devils Bowling
February 20 at 4:03 PM ·

We competed at the districts tournament today at Beaver Vu. The boys bowled well all day long. Ian Carpenter had a 615 series. CaseyKuhl had a 598 series. Every boy bowler bowled at least a 200+ game. They tied the school record for high baker game. In the end the boys finished in 5th place overall. Missing going to state as a team by 2 pins. Great season boys.

Girls had a great time and bowled well. Caitlyn Prince has the high series of 516 and (way to go) Makayla Lawson had a 506 series.

Another great season is in the books.

Reading Blue Devils Bowling
February 4 at 8:16 PM ·

It was another great day to be a Blue Devil. We took on Seven Hills tonight.

The boys won by a total of 4 pins. It came down to the last baker game and senior Jacob Daniels had to throw the first two strikes in the 10th frame. Under pressure Jacob came through with a double in the 10th. Mr. Clutch. He also lead the boys with a high game of 209 and the high series of 392.

The girls also won tonight. Lead by Mak Morgan who had the high game of 177 and the high series of 331.

Tomorrow we travel to Western Bowl for our last CHL match of the season against Taylor.

shared_text:
Coach Lisle
February 2 at 12:00 AM ·

You want to win the Championship? Ask yourself these questions then.

1) What sacrifices am I willing to make to achieve my goals?
2) What talents & skills do I have to acquire?
3) Whom do I have to work with to accomplish it?
4) What problems am I going to have to overcome?
5 What kind of choices am I going to make between now & achieving my goal?
- Lou Holtz

shared_text:
Reading Blue Devils Bowling
January 29 at 7:49 PM ·

It was a great night for Blue Devil bowling. We had a tri-match against Mariemont and Seven Hills.

Boys pulled out the victory over both teams clipping Seven Hills by 3 pins. They remain undefeated in the CHL by beating Mariemont.

Jeremy Easter lead the team with a 259 and a 231 for a career high 490 series. Ian Carpenter added a 238 game and a 404 series. Zach Schueler averaged a 183 in today’s match.

Girls had their best match of the year with a 2092 total. Beating both teams.

Makayla Lawson lead the girls with a 203 high game and a 379 high series. The 379 is Makayla’s career high. Mak Morgan added a 187 game and a 312 series. Caitlyn Prince pitches in with a 311 series. Bri Smyth added a 159 game.

Eric Slavey lead the boys JV with a 156 game and a 300 series.

Congrats to all the high rolling tonight.

We are at the CHL Classic Saturday at Madison.

Monday we celebrate our Seniors at Crossgate against North College Hill.

Vote: Greater Cincinnati, Northern Kentucky high school athletes of the week, Jan. 13
text:
Vote For our Reading wrestlers for an outstanding showing this past weekend at the Charlie Moore Invitational! Nine of our wrestlers placed and the Blue Devils finished second overall in the tournament which was held at Reading High School.

Reading senior wrestler Orlando Smith finished first in his weight class at the Charlie Moore. He is currently ranked #1 in the city in his weight class and advanced to a 17-5 record so far this season.

Orlando is in the running for the Enquirer's wrestler of the week and needs your vote! You can vote once per hour per device at the link below until Friday at 5 p.m.

Let's support Orlando and RHS Blue Devil Wrestling!

shared_text:
Reading Blue Devils Bowling
January 13 at 8:03 PM ·

Jeremy Easter had the high series with a 418. Casey Kuhl had the high game with a 246. He had a perfect game going into the 8th frame. The boys broke the school record for best single team game with a 1056, and broke the record for highest 2 game series with a 1967. Special shout out to Zach Schueler for his highest game of the year. The boys beat Deer Park 2635 to 2270. This clinches a share of the CHL title as the boys remain undefeated in the CHL. They can clinch the CHL title when they take on Mariemont.

The girls fought hard but fell short. The girls remain in second place in the CHL.

The girls were lead by Makayla Lawson who had a 167 high game and 324 high series.

Skylee Meinking also added a 158 game and a 303 series.
